    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1621"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1621">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/130.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to acknowledge receipt of
                    your kind note of the 2nd inst. informing me of the release of Mr. C. Garcin, a
                    French merchant who had been arrested at San Luis Potosí.</p>
                <p>Will you be so good as to convey the expression of my very sincere thanks to Mr.
                    Bonney for the useful help he kindly lent the French <pb facs="1181" n="1065"
                        xml:id="pg_1065"/> Consular Agent and which resulted in the liberation of my
                    compatriot.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
